  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR 2-Promoting quality access to mental health care and rights of PwMD</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is an advocacy initiative that will provide evidence to uncover abuses at 60 traditional mental health centres and get duty bearers to devise national level strategy and response to address abuses to improve treatment for persons with mental disabilities in traditional mental health centres.

This will inform the development of a national protocol on the treatment of persons with mental disabilities in traditional mental health centres throughout Ghana. 

An immediate result of the foregoing will be to minimize the human rights abuses in sixty mental health centres and improve access to health and psychosocial support for persons with mental disabilities in traditional mental health centres. 

It will further strengthen civic consciousness on mental health amongst members of 120 communities in the 30 districts on mental healthcare and human rights of persons with mental disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022; Conduct consultative Meeting (National Stakeholders Meeting). 
&#x2022; Conduct research on human rights violations in traditional mental health centres (Consultancy)
&#x2022; One-on-one meetings with key stakeholders (15 times) 
&#x2022; Conduct Technical working group (TWG) meetings to supervise the development of protocol (4 times)
.Develop an operational protocol for traditional mental centres (Consultancy) 
&#x2022; Celebration of Mental Health Day (annually for three years) 

&#x2022; Organize training workshop for operators of traditional mental health centres, community health psychiatric nurses and MHA visiting committees on mental health and stigma and the SMS platform for monitoring mental health treatment at traditional mental health centres in ten (10) regions</narrative>
  </description>
